  "text": "This is the ®rst study, to our knowledge, that evaluates the effect of withholding gonadotrophins during COS in women at risk of developing OHSS on follicular¯uid levels of VEGF in individual follicles of varying sizes in relation to the granulosa cell number, oocyte retrieval, fertilization and embryo quality. Whilst the ideal control group of women would have been those identi®ed as at risk of developing OHSS but not coasted, this was not ethically possible since coasting has been successfully used to prevent severe OHSS in our unit for a number of years [CITATION_1] . We therefore selected a group of optimally responding women that excluded all poor and hyper-responders.",
